'''Offshoot Films''' is a [[Suffolk]]-based [[digital media]] company.<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=LSN Eastern Region Network|title=Explore and Engage: Creative and Media Diploma Event|url=http://www.diploma-support.org/system/files/LSN%20Creative%20and%20Media%20event%204%20Jun.doc|accessdate=1 December 2009}}</ref> Formed in 2006,<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=Offshoot Films|title=Offshoot Films|url=http://www.offshootfilms.com/|accessdate=1 December 2009}}</ref> the company provided [[film editing]] facilities for such [[Cinema of Australia|Australian]] films as ''[[The Last Days of Chez Nous]]'' and ''[[Spotswood (film)|Spotswood]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=[[Internet Movie Database]]|title=Offshoot Films|url=https://www.imdb.com/company/co0020443/|accessdate=1 December 2009}}</ref> The company also provided [[video production]]s for high schools such as [[Ipswich High School (Suffolk)|Ipswich High School]] and [[Whitton School]].<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=ecomparison|title=About Offshoot|url=http://www.ecomparison.co.uk/offshoot/|accessdate=1 December 2009}}</ref> One such production, made by students at [[Sudbury Upper School]] and [[Great Cornard Upper School]], was a commercial urging high school students to make the choice of post-secondary education or training that best suits them.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Advert promoting Suffolk’s changing world of education launches in local cinemas|date=15 December 2009|publisher=[[Suffolk County Council]]|url=http://www.suffolk.gov.uk/News/NewsArchive/2009December/SuffolkCinemaAdverts.htm|accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref> Offshoot has partnered with primary schools as well to found a project which allows students from the ages of five to eleven create their own films and take them home on DVDs.<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=Felixstowe TV|author=Giles Meehan|title=East Of England Co-op Offers A New Learning Opportunity|date=30 October 2009|url=http://www.felixstowetv.co.uk/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4193&Itemid=0|accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref> In June 2009, Offshoot presented a workshop about education and media at Explore and Engage, a Creative and Media Diploma Event hosted by [[Learning and Skills Network|LSN]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Explore and Engage: Creative and Media Diploma Event|url=http://www.diploma-support.org/system/files/LSN%20Creative%20and%20Media%20event%204%20Jun.doc|accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref>

