[[File:SR20 pyranometer 1.jpg|thumb|A modern pyranometer, shown here is model SR20]] A '''solarimeter''' is a [[pyranometer]], a type of [[measurement|measuring]] device used to measure combined direct and diffuse [[solar radiation]]. An integrating solarimeter measures energy developed from solar [[radiation]] based on the absorption of heat by a [[black body]]. The principle this instrument was designed on was first developed by the Italian priest, Father [[Angelo Bellani]]. He invented the [[Actinometer|actinometric]] method which is based on physical and chemical techniques.<ref>{{cite web | title =Figure 8. Integrating solarimeter | work =NOAA Ship Collection | publisher =National Oceanic & Atmospheric Administration | url =http://www.photolib.noaa.gov/htmls/ship4461.htm | accessdate =2015-02-12 }}</ref>
